        "content": "### NSRI Structure and Mission\n\nWeb: [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: info@searescue.org.za\n\n#### Volunteer Crew and Drowning Statistics\n\n![Volunteer Crew members](images/Intro_Course_Notes_-_HQ-2020_p6_img2.jpeg)\n\nWe estimate that there are more than 2,000 South Africans that drown every year, with many more injured and suffering permanent disability. This makes drowning a significant cause of injury and death, which helps us focus and believe in our mission.\n\n#### Structure of the NSRI\n\nThe NSRI is managed by a core group of executives supported by personnel accountable to the membership (Volunteers) of 1,300 in General Meeting and the Governance Board of 9 members.\n\nWe operate from a central head office in Cape Town, with forty-one rescue bases and 5 satellite stations, creating a geographic footprint of services along a coast of almost 3,000 km and 1,300 km on inland dams.\n\nIn 2019/20, there were 1,300 volunteers, 96 rescue craft, and 44 rescue vehicles.",
