        "content": "### NSRI Volunteer Roles and Responsibilities\n\nWeb: [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: info@searescue.org.za\n\n#### Lifeboat Circle\n\nThe Lifeboat Circle is the NSRI's Society of Retired Persons and Bequestors. It was formed to ensure that the NSRI's efforts to save lives on South African waters continue in perpetuity. This is achieved by encouraging supporters to leave a bequest or legacy to Sea Rescue in their Will, rather than making monthly payments from their retirement savings.\n\n#### Shore Crew\n\nThose who don\u2019t wish to go to sea or have reached the age limits can continue serving as shore crew. They can serve as rescue vehicle operators, base radio operators, plotters, and control room operators. Individuals with specialized knowledge who are willing to donate their expertise for maintenance, repairs, training, and administration are also welcome to join as shore crew. The term \"shore crew\" collectively refers to everyone who serves in a non-sea-going capacity.\n\n#### Sea Crew\n\nCrew members who meet the requirements, live within an appropriate travel time to the base, and have the flexibility in terms of work and available time on weekends to train and volunteer, can serve as sea-going crew.\n\n![Volunteer Sea-going crew during training](images/Intro_Course_Notes_-_HQ-2020_p9_img2.jpeg)",
