        "content": "### Rescue Vessels and Vehicles\n\nWeb: www.searescue.org.za | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: info@searescue.org.za\n\n#### 10.3 Class 4 Vessels\n\n![Class 4 JetRib](images/Intro_Course_Notes_-_HQ-2020_p18_img3.jpeg)\n\nThese are the smaller single-engine vessels, which include 4.7m, 4.2m, and \"Rescue Runners\" (Jet skis). They operate close to the surf line during daylight hours only.\n\n#### 10.4 Rescue Vehicles\n\n![Rescue vehicles](images/Intro_Course_Notes_-_HQ-2020_p18_img4.jpeg)\n\nThe majority of NSRI stations operate 4-wheel drive rescue vehicles as mobile NSRI control centres and coastal search units. RVs are invaluable in liaising with other Search and Rescue units ashore such as the SAPS, emergency medical services, coast watches, and members of the public. They are also used to tow the smaller rescue boats and Quad Bike/Rescue Runner combos to suitable coastal launch sites rather than launch from the station base.",
