        "id": "pre-sea_training_course_notes_ch7",
        "title": "Life Jacket Safety Guidelines",
        "content": "### Life Jacket Safety Guidelines\n\n![The correct way to fasten a life jacket](images/Pre-sea_Training_Course_Notes_p8_img2.jpeg)\n\nThe law requires that on small vessels, a life jacket or buoyancy aid, also known as Personal Flotation Devices (PFDs), shall be worn by all crew and passengers when the vessel is proceeding through surf, heavy turbulent waters, or under inclement weather conditions. The skipper/coxswain makes the decision.\n\n**Important points to remember:**\n\n- Only life jackets approved by the South African Maritime Safety Authority (SAMSA) and the National Regulator for Compulsory Standards (NRCS) may be used on South African registered/licenced vessels. The SAMSA and SANS markings must be on the life jacket.\n\n---\n\nWeb: [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za)",
