        "id": "pre-sea_training_course_notes_ch13",
        "title": "Types of Fire Extinguishers",
        "content": "### Types of Fire Extinguishers\n\n#### 5.3.1 Water \u2013 Red Label\n\n![Water-based fire extinguisher](images/Pre-sea_Training_Course_Notes_p14_img2.png)\n\nWater-based fire extinguishers can be used on paper, wood, and textile fires.\n\n**Advantages:**\n1. It is the cheapest extinguisher available for its size.\n\n**Disadvantages:**\n1. It cannot be used on electrical fires since water conducts electricity.\n2. Water in the quantity supplied by the hand extinguisher is not very effective on man-made fibres, plastics, rubber, and various other substances.\n3. The full extinguisher can weigh up to 15kgs.\n4. The extinguisher is epoxy coated inside; however, even the smallest hole in the coating will cause the extinguisher to rust. When the extinguisher is operated, this rust could block the nozzle.\n\n---\n\nFor more information, visit [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) or contact via email at [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za).",
