        "id": "pre-sea_training_course_notes_ch30",
        "title": "Self-righting Gear Procedure",
        "content": "### Self-righting Gear Procedure\n\nWhen activating the Self-righting Gear, the following procedure must be observed:\n\n- **Account for All Persons**: Ensure all individuals are accounted for. If anyone is missing, check under the vessel.\n- **Move to the Stern**: All persons should move to the stern as a group, maintaining a connection with the vessel and each other by using the grab lines.\n- **Deploy the Swim Line**: Retrieve and deploy the swim line. Everyone must hold onto this line and move approximately 5 meters away from the vessel. It is crucial to maintain contact with the vessel, as the wind could blow it away faster than a swimmer could reach it.\n- **Activate the Gear**: The coxswain or a designated person should retrieve the activating handle on its short line, moving quickly away while holding the swim line. Activate the gear with a strong, steady pull on the line, avoiding a violent jerk.\n\n![Capsize self-righting](images/Pre-sea_Training_Course_Notes_p31_img2.jpeg)\n\nFor more information, visit [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) or contact via email at [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za).",
