        "id": "trainee_crew_module_1_ch4",
        "title": "Safety Protocols at Sea",
        "content": "### Safety Protocols at Sea\n\nWeb: [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za)\n\n#### Video 1: Kill switches\n\n#### 2.3 Buddy System\nWhen out at sea as part of a crew, pair up with another crewman to assist each other in any task you may have, to support each other in a rough sea, and to watch out for each other if you get into difficulty.\n\n#### 3. Limbs Over-side\nA crewperson on a fast rescue boat traveling at speeds of up to 35 knots (64 km per hour) must either be sitting or standing in a secure position, making use of foot straps and/or hand holds to brace themselves against any severe and unexpected movements when at sea.\n\nLearn to expect the unexpected.\n\n![Trainee Crew Module](images/Trainee_Crew_Module_1_p5_img3.jpeg)",
