        "id": "trainee_crew_module_1_ch5",
        "title": "Safety Precautions on Vessel",
        "content": "### Safety Precautions on Vessel\n\nAny person sitting on the pontoons or deck edge with legs over the side will not fulfill this requirement. Even at lower speeds, legs hanging in the water as the vessel rolls or makes a turn will experience considerable drag\u2014possibly enough to pull the person over the side, especially if they are caught unaware with no proper handhold.\n\nNever use your limbs as a fender between the vessel and the quay or another vessel\u2014they will be crushed!\n\n---\n\n![Safety Diagram](images/Pre-sea_Training_Course_Notes_p1_img1.jpeg)\n\n---\n\nFor more information, visit [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) or contact via email at [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za).\n\n---",
