        "id": "trainee_crew_module_1_ch9",
        "title": "Safety Equipment and Gear",
        "content": "### Safety Equipment and Gear\n\nWeb: [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za)\n\n#### Light\n- Lifejackets are fitted with lights to increase visibility during night-time or in a Man Overboard (MOB) situation.\n\n#### Whistle\n- A whistle can be used to attract attention at sea. It is especially important because shouting becomes difficult when hypothermic.\n\n#### Wetsuit\nWetsuits provide thermal aid as heat loss in water is 22 times faster than in air. They also offer insulation against bumps and scrapes on rocks or vessels and provide sun protection.\n\n#### Booties / Footwear\n- Rescue locations can be hazardous with broken glass, sharp rocks, and barnacles. Proper foot protection is essential to avoid injury.\n\n#### Medical Gloves\n- It is advisable to keep medical gloves in a wetsuit or lifejacket pocket for easy access when needed.\n\n#### Knife\n- A personal knife is recommended for all crew members. It should be kept sharp and ready for emergencies, such as cutting lines.",
