        "id": "trainee_crew_module_1_ch10",
        "title": "Safe Handling of Ropes",
        "content": "### Safe Handling of Ropes\n\nWhen working with any ropes, always take care not to place your hand between the rope and a bollard, cleat, or post. A seemingly slack rope can suddenly become tight should the vessels surge. Do not get your fingers caught in the loops of a rope when tying knots.\n\n![Correct and Incorrect Ways to Hold a Rope](images/Trainee_Crew_Module_1_p11_img2.jpeg)\n\nRemember that ropes can part violently when under tension. Learn to expect it, as it is the best way to prevent it from injuring you or someone else.\n\n---\n\nWeb: [www.searescue.org.za](http://www.searescue.org.za) | Tel: 021 434 4011 | Email: [bretta@searescue.org.za](mailto:bretta@searescue.org.za)",
